Every image you’ve ever generated, every thumbnail, every avatar, every weird AI art experiment transforming you into a new style like this, or meme, was made one of two ways.

It was either sculpted from noise. Or written one piece at a time, like a sentence. That’s it. Only two families. And every tool you use, Midjourney, ChatGPT, Nano Banana, FLUX, falls into one of them.

Most people think AI image generators work by searching a giant database and stitching pieces together. Like a smart Google Images collage.

And that’s a big misconception.
